nt of   Hasting   with Middle English genitival <i>-s</i>.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó hOistín</b> ‘descendant of <i>Oistín</i>’, the Gaelic form of the personal name <i>Augustine</i> (see   Austin  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Hasting","meanings":["English: from the Norman personal name <i>Hastang</i>, <i>Hastenc</i>, <i>Hasten</i> (Old Norse <i>Hásteinn</i> ‘high’ + ‘stone’). See also   Hastings  ."]},{"name":"Heston","meanings":["English: habitational name from Heston (Middlesex) or Histon (Cambridgeshire). The Middlesex placename derives from Old English <i>hǣs</i> ‘brushwood’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’, while the Cambridgeshire placename may derive from Old English <i>hyse</i> ‘shoot, tendril’, also ‘son, youth’, + <i>tūn</i>.","Irish (Mayo): variant of   Hastings  ."]}]},{"name":"Amica","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Peaceful, secure’; name of the Prophet's mother."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Amica De Hastings was born in 1245, in Fersfield, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. She married Robert de Bois in 1265, in Norfolk, England. They were the parents of at least 5 sons. She died in 1288, in Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 43."},"et":{"1245–1288":"1245–1288","1230–1298":"1230–1298","1269–1311":"1269–1311","1270–1335":"1270–1335","1272–1351":"1272–1351","1274–Male":"1274–Surnud","1276–Male":"1276–Surnud","1274":"1274","1351":"1351","1230":"1230","1272":"1272","1270":"1270","Abt 1272":"umbes 1272","1335":"1335","1269":"1269","1245":"1245","1311":"1311","1288":"1288","1265":"1265","1276":"1276","1298":"1298","about 1269":"umbes 1269","Abt 1270":"umbes 1270","about 1276":"umbes 1276","about 1274":"umbes 1274","of Feresfield, Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England","Fersfield, Norfolk, England":"Fersfield, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Kent, England":"Kent, England","Of,, Ke